You need to adjust your application to authenticate via IdentityServer first. Remove all the ASP.NET Core Identity logic related to registration, login etc. assuming all of that will be done on IdentityServer side. Then implement the instance of `IClaimsTransformation` which will either replace your current `ClaimsPrincipal`or add additional identities to it if needed with the claim values you want (populated from local database). Here is the example:

&lt;!-- language: c# --&gt;

    public class MyClaimsTransformer : IClaimsTransformation
    {
        public Task&lt;ClaimsPrincipal&gt; TransformAsync(ClaimsPrincipal principal)
        {
            var claims = new List&lt;Claim&gt;();
            claims.Add(new Claim(...)); // put here your claim type and value

            var identity = new ClaimsIdentity(claims);
            principal.AddIdentity(identity);
            return principal;
        }
    }

Then register your claims transformer in IOC in `Startup.ConfigureServices` method:

&lt;!-- language: c# --&gt;

    services.AddTransient&lt;IClaimsTransformation, MyClaimsTransformer&gt;();

